  }, `In order to understand the selection and placement of these purchased film clips within HOD, we turned to the earliest draft of HOD, a document that provides insights into the thematic design of the river on which Marlow and his crew travelled. In the draft, Welles claims that the river was “the single most important aspect of the story” (early script). It is important to note that this script was written before the Nazis invaded Poland and aspects of Nazism and fascism manifested themselves into the script and characters like Kurtz. Because of this, Welles paid an incredible amount of attention to the river. `), React.createElement(MDXTag, {
